				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$K_{p} = K_{p,298} \cdot \frac{T}{298} \cdot \exp \left[ {\frac{{Q_{v} }}{R}\left( {\frac{1}{T} - \frac{1}{298}} \right)} \right]{ },$$\end{document} where Qv is the enthalpy of vaporization of the sub-cooled (super-cooled) liquid, R is the gas constant and Kp,298 is the value of Kp at 298 K. The corresponding values Kp,298 and Qv of anthraquinone and anthracene are derived by regression of in situ particulate mass fraction measurements (see Supplementary Text for detailed description). The gas/particulate partitioning of anthraquinone affects its dry and wet deposition.
